+    ## Prose Quality
+
+    Any non-code text you write (comments, docstrings, error messages, documentation, commit messages) must sound like a person wrote it. Avoid AI-isms: no "serves as", "leverages", "ensures", "facilitates", no significance inflation ("crucial", "pivotal"), no filler ("in order to", "it is important to note"), no sycophantic tone. Be direct and specific.
+
+    ## Document Decision Trade-offs
+
+    When you make a choice not specified in the plan (library, pattern, data structure, approach):
+    - Briefly note the alternatives you considered and why you chose this one
+    - Include in your report under "Self-review findings"
+    - If the decision is significant (affects architecture, performance, or API surface), flag your report as DONE_WITH_CONCERNS so the controller can review the trade-off
+
+    Small decisions (variable naming, loop vs map, etc.) don't need documentation.
